main event: Three unidentified objects were observed flying at 600 MPH at an altitude of 4000' over Adak, Alaska on 16 May 1949.
interesting points: The objects were observed heading South with no reported sound or odor.
No physical evidence or photographs were provided to support the observation.
The conclusion drawn was that the objects appeared to resemble jet aircraft due to the reflection of the sun, but no conclusive shape could be determined.
The weather conditions at the time of the observation included scattered clouds at 3,500 feet with 20 miles visibility.
The document handling instructions and declassification notice indicate that this was a government UFO report that was downgraded and declassified after a specific period.
sighted object: three unidentified objects flying at 600 MPH
